---
By: Seneca
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 223
    Verse: 6
Tags:
  - Happiness
---
True happiness is to understand our duties toward God and man; to enjoy the
present, without being anxious about the future; not to amuse ourselves
with hopes and fears, but to rest satisfied with what we have.
